dt-option:
	searchPanes.emptyMessage
	Set Custom Empty Message
	SearchPanes 1.0.0



            By setting the `-init searchPanes.emptyMessage` option to a string, any cells found in the table will be represented in the pane by that string.



	<default value="No Data">
        The default value for the `-init searchPanes.emptyMessage` paramater is `No Data`. Meaning that as standard empty characters will be represented in the pane by that message.


        As standard, empty cells will be represented in the panes by the string of `-init searchPanes.emptyMessage`.

		This is useful as it means that the panes display the options in a more pleasing way than just having a blank cell.





 $(document).ready(function() {
    var dt = $('#example').DataTable( {
        searchPanes:{
            emptyMessage:"<i><b>EMPTY</b></i>",
        },
		dom: 'Sfrtip',
    });
});
